The paper discusses the complexity of network structures, which is a topic that can fall under several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) since the paper specifically mentions food webs as an example of a network structure. The next likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) since the paper proposes a new representation language for encoding network structures. The third likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) since the paper discusses the use of compression algorithms to measure network complexity. The fourth likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) since the paper mentions the creation of artificially generated food webs using evolutionary processes. The fifth likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory) since the paper uses the "complexity is information content" paradigm to measure network complexity.
